records.addlTxt:
The State files an Amended Information charging four counts of misdemeanor possess THC, contrary to Section 961.41(3g)(e) of the Wisconsin Statutes.  
GUILTY pleas entered to all four counts in the Amended Information.  Convicted.
Sentence is withheld and the defendant is placed on probation to DOC for two (2) years.
Conditions of probation:
1) spend forty-five (45) days in the county jail, under the Huber Law, on count 1 only, commencing on 02-16-16 by 8:00 a.m.  Medical release is allowed;
2) AODA assessment and follow through;
3) assessment, treatment, counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) submit to random urine screens and pay for same;
5) pay court costs;
6) pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Attorney Grieve motions to seal any part of the testimony that mentions the defendant's medical issues, including any portion of the transcript.  Motion granted.
Minutes.
